Advance width 'thinspace' 66 is smaller than 'space' 166, but should be 60% of space '99.6'. Please verify if this is intend to be like it is.

Grenze Gotisch Thin Regular (GrenzeGotisch-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GrenzeGotisch-Thin', Everything looks good.

Grenze Gotisch Thin Regular (GrenzeGotisch-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze Gotisch' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Grenze Gotisch Thin'.

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'GrenzeGotisch-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze Gotisch' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Grenze Gotisch ExtraLight'.

Grenze Gotisch Light Regular (GrenzeGotisch-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GrenzeGotisch-Light', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze Gotisch' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Grenze Gotisch Light'.

Grenze Gotisch Regular (GrenzeGotisch-Regular.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GrenzeGotisch-Regular', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze Gotisch Medium Regular (GrenzeGotisch-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze Gotisch' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Grenze Gotisch Medium'.

Pass

MS NID 6

NID 6 is 'GrenzeGotisch-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze Gotisch' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Grenze Gotisch SemiBold'.

Grenze Gotisch Bold (GrenzeGotisch-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GrenzeGotisch-Bold', Everything looks good.

Grenze Gotisch ExtraBold Regular (GrenzeGotisch-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GrenzeGotisch-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze Gotisch' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Grenze Gotisch ExtraBold'.

Grenze Gotisch Black Regular (GrenzeGotisch-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'GrenzeGotisch-Black', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze Gotisch Black Regular (GrenzeGotisch-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze Gotisch' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Grenze Gotisch Black'.
